      "impact": "",
      "mitigationPath": "",
      "decisionRationale": "A geo-disaster recovery paired namespace is provisioned in Central US. Failover is manual, initiated by the Infra & DevOps on-call engineer following RUNBOOK-SB-02. Producers buffer locally for up to 5 minutes before failing the originating request during a regional outage. Recovery time is bounded by the time to initiate failover and update DNS; tested during the annual DR exercise. In-flight messages not yet acknowledged at failover time may be lost \u2014 this is an accepted risk for event-driven workloads.\n",
      "relatedDecisionRecords": [],
